  "business_context": "Membership records track who is currently a member, at what level, since when, and through when. They drive member-only access (newsletters, events, content), renewal workflows (membership-expiring notices), and member-engagement reporting (retention rate, lapse rate, lifetime membership value). Modeling varies significantly across systems: CiviCRM has a first-class Membership entity with rich support for membership types, levels, statuses (New / Current / Grace / Expired / Pending / Cancelled / Deceased), and renewal rules. NPSP supports Memberships via Opportunity Record Types (with auto-renewal logic), plus a Level object for member-level definitions. Bloomerang doesn't have native Membership but allows it via Custom Fields on Constituent. The B2B systems generally don't have it. Dues payments are typically tracked as Donations linked to the Membership record. When interviewing clients, surface \"Membership\" by asking whether they have members (in any sense), whether membership is time-bound (does it expire), and whether dues drive renewal cycles. Different from a \"donor\" — donors give without expecting transactional benefits; members give in exchange for an enrolled status that confers rights or benefits.",
